4 SYNOPSIS:
5 Under existing law, an awarding authority
6 desiring to enter into a contract for a public works
7 involving an amount in excess of $100,000 is required
8 to advertise for sealed bids and generally follow the
9 requirements of the public works law for the award of
10 the contract.
11 Existing law allows certain contracts to be
12 awarded without following the public works competitive
13 bidding requirements.
14 This bill would expand the current exception to
15 allow an awarding authority to make purchases of
16 materials or equipment pursuant to a cooperative
17 purchasing agreement, the requirements for which are
18 regulated by existing law.
19
20
21 A BILL
22 TO BE ENTITLED
23 AN ACT
24
25 Relating to public works contracts; to amend Section
26 39-2-2, Code of Alabama 1975, as last amended by Act 2025-383,
27 2025 Regular Session, to provide an exception to the public
28 works law for the purchase of certain materials and equipment
Page 1

works law for the purchase of certain materials and equipment
