29 made pursuant to a cooperative purchasing agreement.
30 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
31 Section 1. Sections 39-2-2, Code of Alabama 1975, as
32 last amended by Act 2025-383, 2025 Regular Session, is amended
33 to read as follows:
34 "§39-2-2
35 (a)(1) Before entering into any contract for a public
36 works involving an amount in excess of one hundred thousand
37 dollars ($100,000), the awarding authority shall advertise for
38 sealed bids, except as provided in subsection (k).
39 (2)a. If the awarding authority is the state, a county,
40 or an instrumentality thereof, it shall advertise for sealed
41 bids at least once each week for three consecutive weeks in a
42 newspaper of general circulation in the county or counties in
43 which the improvement, or some part thereof, is to be made.
44 b.1. If the awarding authority is a municipality, or an
45 instrumentality thereof, it shall advertise for sealed bids at
46 least once in a newspaper of general circulation published in
47 the municipality where the awarding authority is located.
48 2. If no newspaper is published in the municipality,
49 the awarding authority shall advertise by posting notice
50 thereof on a bulletin board maintained outside the purchasing
51 office and in any other manner and for the length of time as
52 may be determined. In addition to bulletin board notice, the
53 awarding authority shall also send the notice by U.S. mail or
54 electronic mail to the Department of Finance for publication
55 of the advertisement on the centralized website maintained by
56 the department as further described in subsection (c).
