197 (h) If a proposed public works project is acknowledged
198 in writing by the Alabama Homeland Security Department as: (i)
199 having a direct impact on the security or safety of persons or
200 facilities; and (ii) requiring confidential handling for the
201 protection of such persons or facilities, contracts may be let
202 without public advertisement but with the taking of informal
203 bids otherwise consistent with the requirements of this title
204 and the requirements of maintaining confidentiality. Records
205 of bidding and award shall not be disclosed to the public and
206 shall remain confidential.
207 (i) If a pre-bid meeting is held, the pre-bid meeting
208 shall be held at least seven days prior to the bid opening
209 except when the project has been declared an emergency in
210 accordance with subsection (f).
211 (j) The awarding authority may not offer a contract for
212 bidding unless confirmation of any applicable grant has been
213 received and any required matching funds have been secured by
214 or are available to the awarding authority.
215 (k) Notwithstanding subsection (a), the Department of
216 Transportation may enter into contracts for road construction
217 or road maintenance projects that do not involve more than two
218 hundred fifty thousand dollars ($250,000) without advertising
219 for sealed bids, provided the project is listed on the
220 publicly accessible website of the department for at least
221 seven calendar days before entering into the contract. The
222 total cost of all projects not subject to advertising and
223 sealed bids pursuant to this subsection may not exceed one
224 million dollars ($1,000,000) in the aggregate per year.
